    âI am Miss Grant, sib to the Advocate:
    You, I believe, are Dauvit Balfour.â

I told her how much astonished I was by her genius.

âAnd what do you call the name of it?â she asked.

âI do not know the real name,â said I.  âI just call it _Alanâs air_.â

She looked at me directly in the face.  âI shall call it _Davidâs air_,â
