man was mair just than set with his position.  He had glints of the glory
of the kirk; there were whiles when his dander rase to see the Lordâs
sants misguided, and shame covered him that he should be haulding a
canâle (or carrying a firelock) in so black a business.  There were
nights of it when he was here on sentry, the place aâ wheesht, the frosts
