I could say no more than just âO!â the name of James More always drying
up my very voice.

She was quick to perceive it, and to guess some portion of my thought.

âThere is one thing I must be saying first of all, Mr. David,â said she.
âI think two of my kinsfolk have not behaved to you altogether very well.
And the one of them two is James More, my father, and the other is the
